HEADWORD: Imaum
<hw>I*maum"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Ar. <ets>im⟦amac⟧m</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Among the
Muslims, a minister or priest who performs the regular service of the
mosque.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A Muslim prince who, as a successor of Mohammed,
unites in his person supreme spiritual and temporal power.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imaret</ent>⟦br⟧
